x4freetext: The Errors given in Table are Relative
Errors compounded mainly from Statistical Errors and
Errors in the Analysis Spectra.
Energy Loss in Target. The Loss in Energy
Resolution arising from Landau-Symon Fluctuations is
about one third of the Total Energy Loss in the Target.
.The Uncertainty of Target Thickness.
The Uncertainty in the Collected Charge was not
greater than +- 0.9% for the smallest beam currents.
The Effective Smearing Angle.
Summary of Absolute Errors in Cross Sections
For 10-112 Angular Range.
Summary of Absolute Errors in Cross Sections
For 112-152 Angular Range.
- En-Rsl- The 50 MeV Beam from the Accelerator was
Momentum-Analysed to give an Energy Spectrum with an
approximately Triangular Distribution of base width
100KeV. The resulting beam spot on the Target was 5 mm
wide and 3 mm high and the angular divergence of the
beam was 0.5 degrees vertically and 0.25 degrees
horizontally. After Momentum Analysis the Mean Energy
of the beam as measured by a Monitor was 49.08 MeV.
- By Authors - The Results, which are given in
Data-Sections are uncorrected for the Smearing Effect
caused by the Finite Angular Resolution of the system
and Multiple Scattering in the Target Foil. The
Effective Smearing Angle for this work is +-0.57+-0.01
degrees.
The Errors involved in separating the individual peaks
in each spectrum were negligible for the Elastic 0+ and
First Inelastic 2+ Cross Sections. The 3- Cross
Sections include a small contribution from neighbouring
peaks. The Errors involved are small however (1-1.5%).
More serious Errors occur for the Two-Phonon and other
Weak Cross Sections. The very weak 0+ states, some of
which are not seen at this energy, have been included
with neighbouring (STRONG) states but the effect is
small (< 5%) compared with the Overall Errors in these
Cross Sections (15-20%).

between the dE/dx and Wedge Pulses. The dE/dx Detector
was only slightly shorter than the Wedge Detector and
gave a resolution of approx. 40%, which was more than
sufficient to distinguish protons from other particles.
The Self-Supporting Zn-64 Foil,Thickness 7.45 Mg/Cm**2,
Zn-68 0.26% and Zn-70 0.00%,was Used.
